wdi2-SH.TBS.CURE.ZS.def: Tuberculosis treatment success rate is the percentage of all new tuberculosis cases (or new and relapse cases for some countries) registered under a national tuberculosis control programme in a given year that successfully completed treatment, with or without bacteriological evidence of success ("cured" and "treatment completed" respectively).
wdi2-SH.TBS.CURE.ZS.name: Tuberculosis treatment success rate
wdi2-SH.TBS.CURE.ZS.source: World Health Organization, Global Tuberculosis Report.
